The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Thursday, June 10, 2004 				 Pay-up plea after ligation reverse
Jangipur, June 9: Tota Das, a mother of two who became pregnant after undergoing ligation at a health centre, has moved the Murshidabad consumer disputes redressal forum demanding damages.																								The family of four at Rampura village in Raghunathganj, about 260 km from Calcutta, can hardly afford another member. Totas husband Ashanta earns a meagre living from his grocery. 																								In a complaint lodged on Monday, the Dases named three doctors, including superintendent of Teghari block health centre Asit Dewan, who conducted the faulty ligation last November. The same health centre detected her pregnancy when she went for a check-up. The doctors did not attach any importance to our predicament. We were forced to seek compensation, Ashanta said.
